<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-11T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-11T19:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/549a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-11T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            11, 1928—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>13. The Guatemalan Minister informs the Department that his
                                Government is again protesting to the Government of Honduras against
                                violations of the <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> in the disputed
                                territory, and particularly against the construction of a railway
                                line between Cacao and Chachagualillo.</p>
                            <p>Please investigate and report, ascertaining especially whether any
                                railway construction is being carried on in the disputed
                                territory.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>